- In the context of cricket, a "four" refers to a shot that reaches the boundary of the field without being touched by any fielder, scoring four runs.; 
- A "six" is a shot that clears the boundary of the field without being touched by any fielder, scoring six runs.; 
- The "peak performance year" is considered the most recent year of participation, indicating the player's latest level of performance and involvement in the tournament.
